1. Yes. Set the "parent" attribute of the NPC to move her to a different room. Check it to see which room she is in:
```
if (npc.parent = lounge) {
  msg("'I love the curtains in here, don't you?' says Mary.")
}
else {
  msg("'What is this room?' asks Mary.")
}
```

2. It is generally best to make an object for _anything_ mentioned in a room description, just in case the player decides to look at it. If the description says there is a door with writing on it, some players will type X DOOR or READ DOOR. And OPEN DOOR etc. It is a pain in the neck but makes for a better game.
